<dd class='comment-body' id='Blog1_cmt-162261019822490271'>
<p>
If you've ever wondered what this sort of thing would look like in a more mainstream language, Eric Lippert has just written part 11 in a huge series of posts about  <A HREF="http://blogs.msdn.com/ericlippert/archive/2008/02/12/immutability-in-c-part-eleven-a-working-double-ended-queue.aspx" REL="nofollow">immutability in C#</A>.
</p>
</dd>
